    "created_at": "2015-08-21T00:50:01Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-08-21T00:50:01Z",
    "body": "> Maybe we should add a banner to the start of each file that says what was the current version when it was edited and the time it was edited.\n\nYou can get that information from GitHub's website, and the commit's page also shows the tag names.\n\n> I also think that translations should be put in a separate folder per language (currently the Korean translations are just thrown together with the English files). Something like translations/ko/.\n\nI'm strongly :+1: on this, and we should probably do it sooner than later. Another good thing of it is that translators no longer need to translate the URLs.\n\nFor the folder's name, `docs-translations` could probably be a better name, `translations` indicates they are translations of strings in the source code, which is common for i18n-ed projects.\n"
  },
